Program: Last Word
Title: Robert Robinson, Mother Thelka, Shammi Kapoor, Paul Wilkinson
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b0138zlm
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 21 Aug 2011
Mathew Bannister on Robert Robinson - erudite host of radio's Stop the Week and Brain of Britain and TV's Call My Bluff and Ask the Family Mother Thelka the Greek Orthodox nun who became a muse for the composer Sir John Taverner. He pays tribute. Bollywood's answer to Elvis - Shammi Kapoor Professor Paul Wilkinson who made the study of terrorism a respected academic subject And Marshall Grant who was so much more than a bass player to Johnny Cash. Show less